    <section id="noodles">
        <div class="desc">
          <h2>What Are Noodles?</h2>
          <p>
            Noodles are a type of food made from unleavened dough which is rolled flat and cut, stretched or extruded, into long strips or strings. Noodles can be refrigerated for short-term storage or dried and stored for future use.
          </p>
      </div>
        <div class="desc">
          <h2>How Are Noodles?</h2>
          <p>
            Noodles are usually cooked in boiling water, sometimes with cooking oil or salt added. They are also often pan-fried or deep-fried. Noodle dishes can include a sauce or noodles can be put into soup.
          </p>
      </div>
        <div class="desc">
          <h2>Where From Noodles?</h2>
          <p>
            Noodles are a staple food in many cultures (for example: Chinese noodles, Japanese noodles, Korean noodles, Filipino noodles, Vietnamese noodles, and Italian pasta).
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
